{
  "stem": "22869.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, unbelievable as-- as it was, I come to a city-- I only knew about Katowice in Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But there is a Czech Katowice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we were on the train where the main station was, and all of a sudden American fliers are arriving, thinking in their mind that this is an army train, and start diving at us and shooting.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all hell broke loose.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was-- jumped out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They opened up the-- the-- you know, the wagons there, let us jump out, to take some protection there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there were-- on one side was all fields, and one side was all houses.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So both the SS, the supervising thing, and everybody else, ran out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a free for all like, because they were shooting one after another.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I jumped out of the train, and I hid under a bridge upon which that train just passed, which usually has these big planks for carrying the load of the train, itself.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know the railroad-- what do you call those railroad planks that have really about six by six, eight by eight?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Real heavy stuff.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And on top of this, heavy wood, because it has to stand the load of the train.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And myself and a friend of mine who had the number-- I still remember his name-- Ini Popel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he had-- I had 04-37-014.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had 37-016.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Both of us are hiding under that bridge, and trying to protect ourselves from the bullets.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the meanwhile, some of us were daring and taking jackets off from the concentration camp-- striped jackets-- and throwing it out on the top of the train.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we thought that the-- the Americans will see that this is-- these are guys who are locked up, so they'll stop shooting.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
